HEADWORD: Wesleyanism
<hw>Wes"ley*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>The system of doctrines and church polity inculcated by John
<ets>Wesley</ets> (b. 1703; d. 1791), the founder of the religious sect
called Methodist; Methodism. See <er>Methodist</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
2.</def>⟦br⟧
